# Skill Source Instructions

This folder is the workspace-local source of truth for skills created or improved in this workspace.

## Rules

- Use `smart-skill-maker` as the only skill for creating or improving skills here.
- Keep `skill-creator` installed as part of the required authoring baseline because `smart-skill-maker` builds on it.
- Use `npx skills ...` as the only tool for installing or updating skills in this workspace.
- Do not install workspace skills outside this repo or maintain a second copy as the source of truth.
- Keep source skills under `skills/<role>/<skill-name>/`.
- Keep each skill `name` stable, and track revisions in frontmatter `metadata.skill_version` instead of appending versions to the skill name.
- Increment `metadata.skill_version` every time you update a skill.
- A role is the worker identity and usage scope. Use the role to represent a real worker with related skills and one or more workflows, not just a generic tool label.

## Common flow

1. Create a new skill or improve an existing one under `skills/<role>/<skill-name>/`.
2. Finish the edits in `skills/`.
3. Install or refresh the skill locally in this workspace with:

```sh
npx skills ...
```

## Safety

- Keep secrets out of skill folders.
- Keep reusable assets, scripts, and references inside the source skill folder, not scattered around the repo root.
- If a skill is only half-finished, do not install or refresh it yet.
